                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15551950" author="srowen" created="Thu, 6 Oct 2016 13:39:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;No, the tags actually depend on scalatests&apos;s annotations like TagAnnotation. It wouldn&apos;t compile if they were in test scope.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(Might be better to ask questions on dev@ first)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15551964" author="lucean" created="Thu, 6 Oct 2016 13:45:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s great - thanks for clearing that up. I&apos;ll make sure to post on the mailing list in future.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15752997" author="vanzin" created="Fri, 16 Dec 2016 00:42:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Reopening since this is a real issue (the dependency leaks when you depend on spark-core in maven and don&apos;t have scalatest as an explicit test dependency in your project).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
